This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Country programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children

title.narrative: Programme Budgeting, Planning, Monitoring, Evaluation, and Reporting

description.narrative: PME supported a number of initiatives;including but not limited to preparation of revised work plan matrix; 2021 Annual Management Plan; simplification of operating procedures/guidelines development such as partnerships; expansion of third-party monitoring; support for rapid assessments and resource mobilization; assurance activities; donor reporting; 2022 HAC and Annual Work Plans development and capacity building and alignment of country programme indicators for all sectors. The PF4C evaluation was finalized. While most evaluations including Country Programme Evaluation were paused, the evaluation of the Bright Start health insurance pilot in Yangon townships continues to generate evidence for successful implementation and scale up. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:14/01/2022
